Translator-anon here, it's a lot more complicated than that

Japanese artists are genuinely afraid of their work being spread overseas and yes, while PART of that is because of lost profits and all that, but the main reason is because Japanese copyright laws are WAY different than they are in the US

Companies operating in Japan have the general mindset that fanart is basically free publicity and, as such, as long as the artist isn't making *too* big a profit off of a derivative work (fun fact: this is why most Japanese artists sell fanart "at cost") then they'll turn a blind eye. As such, the self-published art community is fucking huge, because it's basically encouraged by companies to make art of their characters.

However, the second their work enters the eyes of the Western world all bets are fucking off
You're making even a penny selling art of a Disney character? You're about to get sued into the fucking ground by the House of Mouse. Doesn't matter that you didn't intend to sell overseas; it's here now and there's nothing you can do about it, fucko

Very cute drawing.
In south Florida, there really aren't enough bus routes, and almost the whole area is low-density suburban sprawl. To get from point A to point B you might have to walk two miles from point A to the closest bus stop, and after your bus ride, walk a mile from the bus stop to point B. Very unpleasant in the hot and humid climate.
There are also no night routes at all, and buses stop running well before midnight. This means if you want to go home from a fun activity where everyone else is staying until 2 AM, you may need to leave at 9 or 10 PM if you don't want to waste money on Lyft or Uber.
There's no good cluster of points of interest, so even if you're in downtown Fort Lauderdale or Miami, if you're deciding with friends what you want to do, you may end up going "damn, there's literally no bowling alley or arcade in downtown, and the buses are no longer running, and the nearest fun things are miles away"

However, when riding the buses, the buses themselves are quite comfortable and fine, and I feel happy remembering those bus rides.
